  "prompt": "What is a good substitute for chipotle powder?",
  "response": "If you need a substitute for chipotle powder, there are a few options you can consider based on what you have available and your taste preferences:\n\n1. **Smoked Paprika:** This is a great alternative as it also offers a smoky flavor, though it is not as spicy as chipotle powder. You can add a pinch of cayenne pepper for extra heat if desired.\n\n2. **Cayenne Pepper:** If you are mainly concerned with spice rather than smokiness, cayenne pepper can be used. Keep in mind it is hotter than chipotle powder, so use it sparingly.\n\n3. **Sriracha or Hot Sauce:** For a liquid substitute, Sriracha or a similar hot sauce can work in recipes where moisture won\u2019t be an issue. The flavor will be different, but it will provide a spicy kick.\n\n4. **Paprika and Chili Powder Mix:** Combine regular paprika with a bit of chili powder to mimic both the sweetness and the heat of chipotle.\n\n5. **Ancho Chili Powder:** This will provide a similar flavor profile, though it is milder and less smoky. You might want to combine it with some smoked paprika to achieve the desired smokiness.\n\nChoose the option that best fits the recipe and your taste preferences!",
